name: Are You Lonely by Yourself
comments: Also released both under "Make It Easy on Yourself". Chorus changed to: "Are you happy by yourself? Are you lonely by yourself?" Burt Bacharach was furious when he found out The Isley Brothers changed the lyrics, which explains why the track was not released at the time. Another reason might be that recording of this unconventional song wasn't considered a success, since the Isley Brothers had at that point mostly experience with gospel music.
